      <abstract>
        <p>New York State Bar Association forms committee to help lawyers better advise clients who do business over Internet (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The New York State Bar Association has formed a committee to help lawyers better advise clients who do business over the Internet.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The New York State Bar Association has formed a committee to help lawyers better advise clients who do business over the Internet.</p>
        <p>The committee will review case law, legislation and regulations affecting the swiftly developing field of cyberspace law and disseminate the information by sponsoring lectures and panel sessions and distributing reports to the 67,000 members of the association, said Madeleine Schachter, the committee's chairwoman.</p>
        <p>Joseph P. Fried (NYT)</p>
      </block>
